[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Locarno banner.jpg"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Schiffsanleger LagoMaggiore Locarno CH 20110101.JPG"],["thumb"],["400px"],["Lake Maggiore, as seen from Locarno"]]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.locarno.ch\/ Locarno"]}]}," is a city at the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Lake Maggiore"]]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Switzerland"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By car"]},"\n\nFrom the east, take highway A2 ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Basel"]]}," to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Chiasso"]]},", exit at ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bellinzona"]]}," South, direction Locarno. After the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Magadino"]]}," airport, take the A13 highway,direction Locarno. After the tunnel, the first exit will bring you in the center of Locarno. Parking available in the new Piazza Castello parking.\n\nFrom the west, take the road coasting the lake Maggiore, from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Verbania"]]}," trough ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Cannobio"]]}," and the Brissago customs. Then take the A13 highway, direction Locarno. An alternative, from Simplon and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Domodossola"]]},", is the Valle Vigezzo and Centovalli road, direction Locarno.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By train"]},"\n\nRegular trains link Locarno directly with ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Zurich"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Basel"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Lucerne"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Milan"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bellinzona"]]},". The Centovallina train line connects Locarno and the Simplon line (from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Geneva"]]}," or ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bern"]]},").\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By plane"]},"\n\nLugano airport. Then take the bus to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Lugano"]]}," and the train to Locarno.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By bike"]},"\n\nBike rental can be found at the train station (",{"type":"''","value":["Piazza Stazione"]},", Tel. ''+41 91 7436564). Rental fee: CHF30\/day (8AM-7PM).\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["On foot"]},"\n\nMost Of the city of Locarno can be explored on foot. The Main Square Piazza Grande is walking distance from Main Railway station. Old Town of Locarno is behind Piazza Grande.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["Ticino Discovery Card"]},"\n\nWith this card you get access to all major touristic attractions in Ticino canton including unlimited travel on public transport, cable cars, furniculars and museums. Price of the card is 87 CHF. People holding Swiss GA Travel card or Half fare card get 10 CHF discount. Card is valid for 3 days. A real good deal to discover Ticino and is available at major hotels, hostels, train station and Tourist Offices.  ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.cartaturisticaticino.ch"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Piazza Grande"],["content=It is the heart of the city center and also the major shopping area."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Città Vecchia"],["alt=The old town"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Santuario della Madonna del Sasso"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Castello Visconteo"],["content=A castle which today serves as Municipal and Archeological Museum."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=The Casa Rusca Gallery"]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["Walk the Lake Maggiore promenade"]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":["  ",{"type":"{{","value":[["do"],["name=Take boat trips on Lake Maggiore"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.navigazionelaghi.it\/"],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content="]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''"